  "prompt": "How do I solve the following question in HackerRank?",
  "response": "To help you solve a question on HackerRank, I'll need some more details about the specific question you're working on. Here's a general process you can follow to approach solving programming challenges on HackerRank:\n\n1. **Understand the Problem Statement**:\n   - Read the problem statement carefully to understand what is being asked.\n   - Identify the input and output requirements.\n\n2. **Review Sample Test Cases**:\n   - Study the example inputs and outputs provided in the problem statement to understand how the expected solution should work.\n\n3. **Plan Your Approach**:\n   - Think through the logic required to solve the problem. Consider using pseudocode or flowcharts.\n   - Decide on the data structures and algorithms that will help you implement the solution efficiently.\n\n4. **Write the Code**:\n   - Begin coding your solution in your preferred programming language.\n   - Start with a basic version that handles simplest cases if you\u2019re dealing with a complex problem.\n\n5. **Test Your Solution**:\n   - Use the sample test cases provided by HackerRank to ensure your code is working correctly.\n   - Consider edge cases and additional test cases that the problem might not cover explicitly.\n\n6. **Debug if Needed**:\n   - If your solution isn\u2019t working as expected, review your code to identify mistakes or inefficiencies.\n   - Utilize print statements or a debugger to step through your code and examine where it might be going wrong.\n\n7. **Optimize**:\n   - If your solution works but is not efficient, consider optimizing it for better performance.\n   - Revisit your choice of algorithms or data structures if necessary.\n\n8. **Submit Your Solution**:\n   - Once you're confident your code handles all scenarios correctly, submit it on the platform to see if it passes all the test cases.\n\n9. **Review the Feedback**:\n   - If your submission is not accepted, review the feedback or failed test cases to understand what went wrong.\n   - Modify your solution accordingly and try submitting again.\n\nIf you provide specific details about the question, like the problem statement or input/output examples, I can offer more targeted assistance.",
